 Thupeyo Muleya in Beitbridge Police have arrested four dangerous robbers who used knives and machetes to terrorise Beitbridge residents on foot paths at night.  The gang was found hiding in a shack in a bushy area between the Nassa and Zesa complex. Police officers on the scene said the gang was tracked by the canine unit after they had robbed a flea market dealer, near Dulivhadzimo stadium on Wednesday morning.  “We are still investigation to check if they are not linked to several cases of robbery around the town,” said a police source.